d on `but-ctx` so capture can build the same repository/workspace context\n  as the rest of GitButler\n- prefer reusable `but-api` entry points when they already provide the product\n  shape we need\n- use a lower-level path-only worktree snapshot helper for uncommitted files;\n  avoid UI diff APIs that compute hunks, ownership, assignments, or dependency\n  data we do not need\n- use `but_workspace::head_info` or an equivalent unpruned workspace API behind\n  an agentlog-local snapshot adapter for stack/branch snapshots; avoid the\n  legacy `but-api` shape if it prunes the view to the graph entrypoint\n\nThis means the first implementation can capture environment snapshots from the\nsame workspace APIs the app already trusts. If this dependency shape becomes too\ncostly later, it can be replaced behind an agentlog-local snapshot adapter\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:42:33.065Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}